0-10-05","#SS",{"_":435,"when":436,"who":433},"Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages","2020-10-08",{"_":438,"when":439,"who":433},"Simona Stoyanova added EDCS numbers","2020-11-20",{"_":441,"when":442,"who":433},"Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography","2020-11-26",{"_":444,"when":311,"who":445},"Updated Zenodo DOI","#system",{"_":447,"when":448,"who":433},"renumbered files, uris and references","2021-01-19",{"_":450,"when":451,"who":452},"Marta Fogagnolo revised the text encoding, added dimensions, translations and commentary","2022-10-31","#martaf",{"surface":454},{"type":455,"graphic":456},"front",[457,461],{"n":458,"url":97,"height":459,"width":460,"desc":98},"screen","3680px","5520px",{"n":462,"url":463,"height":459,"width":460,"desc":98},"print","ISic001325.jpg",{"body":465},{"div":466},[467,492,501,504,506,516],{"type":120,"xml:space":468,"xml:lang":117,"resp":452,"ab":469},"preserve",{"lb":470,"persName":479,"w":489},[471,473,475,477],{"n":472},"1",{"n":474},"2",{"n":476},"3",{"n":478},"4",[480,487],{"type":481,"name":482,"space":485},"attested",[483,484],"Σοσίᾳ","Ἐλάτῃ",{"quantity":474,"unit":486},"character",{"type":481,"name":488},"Ἀφροδείσιος",[490,491],"γλυκυτάτῃ","σύμβιος",{"type":493,"resp":452,"listApp":494},"apparatus",{"app":495},[496,498],{"note":497},"Text based on photographs",{"loc":499,"note":500},"1-2","Korhonen observes that the name of the deceased could be in the nominative form, but the presence of the attribute suggests that it is dative.",{"type":502,"xml:lang":229,"resp":452,"p":503},"translation","To the sweetest Sosia Elate, Aphrodeisios, her husband.",{"type":502,"xml:lang":389,"resp":452,"p":505},"Alla dolcissima Sosia Elate, Aphrodisios, il marito.",{"type":507,"p":508},"commentary",{"_":509,"foreign":510},"The epitaph presents a less common structure, with the name of the deceased probably in dative and the name of the dedicant in nominative followed by an attribute that qualifies his relationship with the deceased (see Korhonen 2004: 87). To be excluded is the interpretation of the epitaph as two nominatives, the first of the name of the deceased, the latter of the name of the dedicant because of the attribute . The indication of the age of the deceased and the dedication verb is omitted. The gentilicium Sosia testifies that the deceased belonged the gens Sosia; her cognomen  is also attested in an inscription of imperial age from Dikaiarchia-Puteoli (CIL 10.2209). The name of the husband, , is well attested in several inscriptions of South Italy (LGPN 3A: 86).",[511,513,515],{"_":512,"xml:lang":117},"γλυκυτάτη",{"_":514,"xml:lang":117},"Ἐλάτη",{"_":488,"xml:lang":117},{"type":517,"listBibl":518},"bibliography",[519,550],{"type":120,"bibl":520},[521,524,527,530,533,536,541,544,547],{"author":123,"date":124,"citedRange":125,"ptr":522,"ref":523},{"target":127},{"_":129,"target":129},{"author":133,"date":134,"citedRange":135,"ptr":525,"ref":526},{"target":137},{"_":139,"target":139},{"author":143,"date":144,"citedRange":145,"ptr":528,"ref":529},{"target":147},{"_":149,"target":149},{"author":143,"date":153,"citedRange":154,"ptr":531,"ref":532},{"target":156},{"_":158,"target":158},{"author":162,"date":163,"citedRange":164,"ptr":534,"ref":535},{"target":166},{"_":168,"target":168},{"type":172,"n":173,"citedRange":537,"ptr":539,"ref":540},{"ref":538},{"_":176,"target":177},{"target":179},{"_":181,"target":181},{"type":172,"n":185,"citedRange":186,"ptr":542,"ref":543},{"target":188},{"_":190,"target":190},{"type":172,"n":194,"citedRange":195,"ptr":545,"ref":546},{"target":197},{"_":199,"target":199},{"author":203,"date":204,"citedRange":205,"ptr":548,"ref":549},{"target":207},{"_":209,"target":209},{"type":211,"bibl":53},[552],{"n":458,"url":97,"height":459,"width":460,"desc":98,"surfaceType":455},{"title":554,"body":555,"divs":556,"images":573},"ISic001325. Epitaph for Sosia Elate","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"text